{"type":"message","id":"3d66ed7a","parentId":"19966986","timestamp":"2026-04-23T21:03:05.947Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me check the actual route.ts file to see what header it expects.","thinkingSignature":"6c1d6c2cf30d924459b7a176854f8b855cc30a2403bf3d12edb26c8f19e84a4a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_o3s88e2funmw_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/maiy-tech-hub/app/api/cron/publish/route.ts"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":88,"output":69,"cacheRead":20607,"cacheWrite":493,"totalTokens":21257,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776978182474,"responseId":"0639bc079fd15d5c191f5ce363c250a5"}}
{"type":"message","id":"2e496415","parentId":"3d66ed7a","timestamp":"2026-04-23T21:03:05.955Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_o3s88e2funmw_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import { NextResponse } from 'next/server'\nimport { getNextArticleForSlot, markAsPublished, PUBLISH_SLOTS, type QueuedArticle } from '@/lib/content-queue'\n\n// Protect cron endpoints with a secret\nconst CRON_SECRET = process.env.CRON_SECRET || 'maiy-dev-secret'\n\nexport async function POST(request: Request) {\n  // Verify secret\n  const authHeader = request.headers.get('authorization')\n  const secret = authHeader?.replace('Bearer ', '')\n  if (secret !== CRON_SECRET) {\n    return NextResponse.json({ error: 'Unauthorized' }, { status: 401 })\n  }\n\n  const { slot } = await request.json()\n\n  if (!slot || !['noon', 'evening'].includes(slot)) {\n    return NextResponse.json({ error: 'Invalid slot. Use \"noon\" or \"evening\".' }, { status: 400 })\n  }\n\n  const article = getNextArticleForSlot(slot as 'noon' | 'evening')\n\n  if (!article) {\n    return NextResponse.json({\n      success: false,\n      slot,\n      message: `No queued article for ${slot} slot`,\n      timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),\n    })\n  }\n\n  // In Phase 1: mark as published (simulated)\n  // Phase 2: actually write MDX file + trigger revalidation\n  markAsPublished(article.slug)\n\n  // Log for monitoring\n  console.log(`[CRON] Published: \"${article.title}\" (${slot}) at ${new Date().toISOString()}`)\n\n  return NextResponse.json({\n    success: true,\n    published: article,\n    slot,\n    timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),\n  })\n}\n\nexport async function GET() {\n  // Status endpoint\n  const status = PUBLISH_SLOTS.map((s) => {\n    const next = getNextArticleForSlot(s.name)\n    return {\n      slot: s.name,\n      label: s.label,\n      cronVN: s.cronVN,\n      topic: s.topic,\n      nextArticle: next ? { slug: next.slug, title: next.title, scheduledDate: next.scheduledDate } : null,\n    }\n  })\n\n  return NextResponse.json({\n    success: true,\n    status: 'ok',\n    serverTime: new Date().toISOString(),\n    timezone: 'UTC+7',\n    slots: status,\n  })\n}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776978185954}}
{"type":"message","id":"e38cbf06","parentId":"2e496415","timestamp":"2026-04-23T21:03:11.568Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see - this API doesn't accept `scheduledDate` and `slug` directly. Instead it reads from the `content-queue.ts` file and picks the next article for the given slot. I need to:\n\n1. Add the article to the queue first (via content-queue.ts or by manually adding to the queue)\n2. Then call the cron/publish API\n\nBut looking at the API, it takes `slot` and reads from `getNextArticleForSlot(slot)`. Let me check the content-queue.ts to understand how articles are queued.\n\nAlso, looking at the request body, the cron/publish endpoint only takes `slot`. \n\nI need to look at how `getNextArticleForSlot` retrieves articles to understand where I should add the new one.","thinkingSignature":"7f1548cbeec6551599b9f80f2c992f1ce94fa40b65ba9cb2d76eabc41a24c86c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5vynmax0dvkb_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/maiy-tech-hub/lib/content-queue.ts"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":587,"output":210,"cacheRead":20969,"cacheWrite":221,"totalTokens":21987,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776978185958,"responseId":"0639bc0b098b4054dbdc43126934bb7a"}}
